Seven people were killed and hundreds were displaced when the province was lashed by heavy rain earlier this month. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Finance MEC Barbara Creecy says R20 million will be spent on assisting families displaced by the recent flash floods.Creecy has presented the medium-term budget policy statement and the 2016/2017 adjustment budget in the provincial legislature.Seven people were killed and hundreds were displaced when the province was lashed by heavy rain earlier this month.Creecy says the amount will be spent by the Department Of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs. Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs has been allocated R20 million to address the resettlement needs of communities affected by recent floods in the province. WATCH: Alexandra picks up pieces after flood damage(Edited by Shimoney Regter)